node.text:
✨𝕋𝕒𝕣𝕠𝕥 ℝ𝕖𝕧𝕖𝕒𝕝 ✨ 
1. The Eight of Elixirs (Cups) is an invitation to explore new realms. Sometimes in life things might not work out the way we hoped and letting go seems the only option. Removing those things in your life that doesn’t align with your highest purpose is essential. See this as an opportunity to learn and grown! Letting go doesn’t have to be a negative thing, it’s also a chance to ask yourself what brings you fulfilment and contentment and to follow them. It’s a time to explore what makes you truly happy so you can realign your direction with your passion. 

2. The Four of Candles (Wands) can indicate something much like a homecoming to the places and/or people who love and care for you. In numerology, four represents stability and safety, and this is the place your moving to. It’s an invitation to slow down and even pause. You’ve achieved so much, more than your realise, and now is the time to celebrate how far you’ve come and give yourself the credit you deserve.

3. The Moon is a reminder not to take everything at face value. Sometimes we only know half a story and don’t have all the information you need to move forward. Listen to your intuition so you can see beyond what’s in front of you. Feel into situations rather thinking what they mean. Let go of negative self talk and allow your intuition to guide you and give you a greater level of understanding. Feel into situations rather than overthinking what they might mean. Pay attention to your dreams, they can also give you guidance about which direction to go.

✨S𝕖𝕝𝕗 L𝕠𝕧𝕖 S𝕡𝕖𝕝𝕝 J𝕒𝕣 ✨
Self love is definitely something I need a little help with from time to time, so I created another spell jar to help nurture and strengthen these feelings.

In terms of crystals (you don’t have to use any crystal if you don’t have them), clear quartz is a great substitute for the rose quartz. Rhodochrosite is one of my favourite crystals at the moment and it pairs amazingly with rose quartz to give emotional support.

Any of the ingredients can be substituted if you don’t have them, so I definitely encourage you to use what you have around you. Make the magick your own!

Place all the ingredients in a clean jar. All herbs must be 100% dry so the contents don’t mould. Burn a pink (or white) candle, the colour for self love, on top of the lid to completely seal it. Make sure you drop wax all round the seal of the bottle to close it.

Place it somewhere visible to act as a reminder to strengthen the intentions you made with the spell jar. If your jar is small enough, you can carry it with you. 

Keep your jar until you feel it has worked it’s magick or you feel its effect waning. ⁣Return the biodegradable herbs to the Earth by burying them and cleanse the jar and crystal so they can be used again ✨

Lindsay 💜

node.text:
✨S𝕖𝕝𝕗 C𝕒𝕣𝕖 R𝕖𝕧𝕖𝕒𝕝 ✨ 
1. C𝕝𝕖𝕒𝕟 Y𝕠𝕦𝕣 S𝕡𝕒𝕔𝕖 
Giving yourself a clean and tidy space to live and work in has a ripple effect. It can help you declutter your mind as well as decluttering your space. Don’t stay on the surface, clean out cupboards and draws, dust, vacuum and sort out the things you don’t want or need anymore. Notice how a clean space makes your energy feel clearer. Create a routine that will allow you to keep up all your hard work. Do something small each day to help you keep on top of it all and see how much better it makes you feel!

2. C𝕠𝕟𝕟𝕖𝕔𝕥 W𝕚𝕥𝕙 C𝕣𝕪𝕤𝕥𝕒𝕝𝕤 
This never fail to ground me! Crystals are living, sentient beings. They are keepers of wisdom and energy and spending some time to connect (or reconnect) with the crystals you have can help you access this wisdom and energy and channel it into your life. Hold a crystal in your receptive hand while meditating. Feel it’s energy and pay attention to how it makes you feel and any visions that come to mind. Try sleeping with a crystal under your pillow to see how it effects your dreams or carry one with you though out the day to see how it’s energy makes you feel.

3. I𝕟𝕥𝕦𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕠𝕟
Intuition is the insight that comes before thoughts and without thinking. This card is calling you to trust your intuition more. If you’ve been seeing synchronicities  lately but have either ignored or doubting them, now is the time to listen. Try and keep a track of when you receive intuitive messages and how often it turns out to be right. It will help you build up trust in your own intuitive skills.

🌒 L𝕦𝕟𝕒𝕣 H𝕖𝕣𝕓𝕤 🌘
Herbs of the moon can greatly affect our subconscious mind. They help us move past the barriers of the conscious mind and connect us to what is beyond. Their powerful action on our body can help us strengthen the connect with our intuition. Working with lunar herbs can also be useful for magick associated with dream work too.

These herbs have so many magickal uses. They make good tea blends, carried around in a spell pouch, burned as incense and used in spells and rituals that align with the moon.

How do you work with lunar herbs in your Craft? 🌿✨

Lindsay 💜
